<item>
            <title>[HBASE-960] REST interface:  more generic column family configure and also get Rows using offset and limit</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-960</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The update column family operation in REST interface will overwrite the default metadata using the default value which is unexpected.  &lt;br/&gt;
We should use the column family to get the old value and then do update if requested by the users.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, for non-default metadata value, such as &quot;hbase.hregion.majorcompaction&quot;, we should still be enable to create/update it using REST interface.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For RowHandler, the user can request with offset and limit and get the rows.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
